The paper discusses reinforcement learning and value functions, which are commonly studied in the machine learning and artificial intelligence communities (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also discusses control theory and economics, which are relevant to robotics (cs.RO) and systems and control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper introduces a new type of value function called the particle value function, which could be of interest to researchers in the field of mathematical optimization and algorithms (cs.MA).
